title: Utah tops Arizona State to remain unbeaten
text:
Photo: Mark Humphrey, Associated Press Paxton Lynch celebrates with fans after beating Ole Miss, Memphis’ 1st win over a ranked opponent since 1996. Paxton Lynch celebrates with fans after beating Ole Miss,...
SALT LAKE CITY — Travis Wilson threw for 297 yards and two touchdowns and No. 4 Utah held off Arizona State 34-18 on Saturday night to remain the lone undefeated team in the Pac-12.
